When I create tests in different files and at least one of them includes the beforeEach or afterEach hook, those hook gets called for all tests.
You can reproduce this with the following code.

test1.js

module.exports = {
        test1: function () {
            console.log('test1');
        }
};
test2.js

module.exports = {
    beforeEach: function () {
        console.log('beforeEach');
    },
    test2: function () {
        console.log('test2');
    }
};
Then run:

mocha -u exports --recursive .

beforeEach
test1
  ✓ test1
beforeEach
test2
  ✓ test2

  2 passing (8ms)